Adjust racks to middle and top positions and preheat #oven{} to 400 degrees. Line a
#baking sheet{} with #foil{}. Wash and dry produce.

Remove @BBQ Baby Back Ribs{1} from package and place on prepared #sheet{}. Top ribs with any
remaining sauce from package, then sprinkle with half the @Ancho Chili Powder{2%teaspoon} 
(you'll use the rest later). Top ribs with a second sheet of foil; crimp edges of foil
to create a packet.

Mince @Jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds for less heat.

Place @Butter{3%tablespoon} (6 TBSP for 4 servings) in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}. 
Microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}.

In a separate small #bowl{}, combine half the melted butter with @Cream Cheese{2%tablespoon},
half the @Cheddar Cheese{½%cup} (you'll use the rest later), and up to half the jalapeño to taste.

Remove @Buttermilk Biscuits{6%ounce} from package. Using a #rolling pin{}, roll out each
biscuit into a 3-inch round.

Divide cheddar filling among biscuits. Using your fingers, fold over biscuits and
pinch to close. Gently roll each stuffed biscuit into a ball.

Place close together seam sides down on a second lightly oiled baking sheet.

== Bake ==

Place sheet with ribs on middle rack; place sheet with biscuits on top rack.

Bake until ribs are warmed through and biscuits are golden and puffed,
~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep ribs covered until ready to serve.

Remove sheet with biscuits from oven; drizzle with remaining melted butter,
then sprinkle with remaining cheddar and remaining jalapeño to taste.

Return biscuits to top rack until dough is cooked through and cheese has melted,
~{2-3%minutes} more. (It's OK if some cheese oozes out.)

== Chili Lime Corn Salad ==

Meanwhile, drain @Corn{13.4%ounce}; pat dry with #paper towels{}.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
corn and remaining chili powder; cook, stirring occasionally, until corn is charred,
~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: If corn begins to pop, cover pan.

Transfer to a large bowl. Set aside to cool.

> TIP: To help your corn cool down quicker, refrigerate until ready to use in step 5.

== Assemble Corn Salad ==

Dice @Roma Tomato{2}(diced). Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced).
Roughly chop @Cilantro{¼%ounce}(roughly chopped). Zest and quarter @Lime{1}.

Once charred corn has cooled to room temperature (or colder), stir in tomatoes,
scallions, @Smoky Red Pepper Crema{2%tablespoon}, half the @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} (all
for 4 servings), half the cilantro, a squeeze of lime juice, and lime zest to taste.
Season generously with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

== Serve ==

Carefully remove and discard foil from ribs. Transfer ribs to a #cutting board{} and
cut into individual pieces.

Garnish corn salad with remaining cilantro. Serve with biscuit bombs and remaining
lime wedges on the side.